cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SE, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper discusses configuration management in networks with high security demands and proposes a resilient configuration management process to prevent malicious behavior and attacks. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is also likely as the paper focuses on configuration management in networks and proposes a configuration management system. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is relevant as the paper discusses a decentralized configuration management process and uses a distributed ledger and smart contract framework. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper proposes a configuration management system and discusses conflict mediation strategies. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the building blocks of conflict mediation strategies.
